## Task 4: Count Down with a while Loop

**1. What is the role of the line counter = counter - 1;? What would happen without it?**
This line decreases the counter variable during each repetition of the loop. Without it, the value of the counter would never change, meaning the condition `counter > 0` would remain true forever. This traps the Arduino in an infinite loop where it is permanently stuck repeating the same instructions.

